cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.HC 

This paper focuses on human-robot interaction and proposes a deep learning framework for learning interactive tasks through imitation learning. The paper involves the use of deep learning models for motion embedding, prediction, and generation of robot joint trajectories. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also involves the use of deep learning models, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of computer vision techniques for motion analysis, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves the use of predictive and adaptive components, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves the study of human-robot interaction, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
